{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PLAN REVIEW · CONTAINER · [G3] Child coverage — pairing (parent 6f2d ⟶ child 4024 WS-DOC) — VERDICT: CLEAN (no findings).\n\nAuthoritative residual roster = 2 children: WS-DOC (4024) + WS-EVAL-EXISTING (b4af). 4-bucket audit of every parent acceptance/success criterion, with absence cross-checked against the whole roster:\n\nACCEPTANCE:\n1. docs/workflow-engine.md exists, linked from README + CLAUDE.md index, CLIENT-vs-REBAR-DEV split — FULLY (this child, WS-DOC AC1+AC2).\n2. Documents YAML DSL, scripted-vs-agentic, agent-vs-single-turn bright line, three-pass pattern, eval seam (two-tier/live-trigger/cost+fork-safety rails), cross-links llm-framework.md + plan-review-gate.md not-duplicate — FULLY (WS-DOC AC3 covers DSL/scripted-agentic/bright-line/three-pass; AC4 covers eval-seam two-tier+live-trigger+cost/fork-safety; AC5 covers cross-link-don't-duplicate / no-contradiction).\n3. Eval specs for completion-verifier/ticket-quality/spec-alignment, validate_eval_spec-clean, cross-family judge (gates:false), at_least(k)/epochs, coverage threshold, non-empty gold_set — FULLY (sibling b4af AC1).\n4. Deterministic-scorer registry; every scorer name maps to pure fn; validate_scorer rejects unregistered — FULLY (sibling b4af AC2).\n5. run_eval() runs real Inspect eval (no NotImplementedError); 3 agentic reviewers via context-injection solver + stubbed/fixture repo tools — FULLY (sibling b4af AC3).\n6. eval-discipline CI validates all packaged specs every PR, no model call; offline tests assert dataset balance + non-empty gold_set — FULLY (sibling b4af AC4).\n7. eval-live CI on workflow_dispatch + weekly schedule, non-blocking, response-cached, concurrency-capped, fork-safe; spend-cap guidance documented — FULLY (sibling b4af AC5).\n8. Every child ticket closed (each signed by completion-verifier gate) — STRUCTURAL/process (covered-by-definition by the gate-closure process over the 2-child roster; not a content deliverable, not an uncovered finding).\n\nSUCCESS:\nS1. New contributor can read the doc and decide workflow-vs-bespoke-op + how to run/trigger evals, without reading source — FULLY (this child: WS-DOC scope \"when to use a workflow vs a bespoke op\" + AC2 client run/use guidance + AC4 how live tier is triggered).\nS2. Prompt edit to any packaged reviewer prompt is regression-gated by an eval that actually SCORES output, not shape-validates — FULLY (sibling b4af — its stated purpose: \"regression-gated, not a blind cutover\"; run_eval() actually scores rather than shape-validating).\n\nNo parent acceptance/success criterion is left uncovered. The criteria this child (WS-DOC) owns are fully covered by its own ACs; the eval-execution criteria are fully covered by sibling WS-EVAL-EXISTING (b4af) in the roster; the child-closure criterion is structural. Empty findings list for G3 on this pairing."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782579689820728001,"uuid":"71b34369-b1f0-463b-8415-71eac2ec8a7f"}